metadata.name: Sketch A #29
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch A starts very simple. It's the basic grid framework I intend to use for the series. It's just a simple grid with one colored square (usually). Colors are borrowed from Echos/Orbits. Grid size, padding, and line thickness vary.

metadata.name: California Hills in Late Sun #35
metadata.description:
This is inspired by a road trip I took up the California coast. There are three color palettes: summer, spring, and black and white.

I designed this to fill your display, up to 3200x1600 pixels, so be sure to try it out in live mode.

Enjoy!

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #535
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.

metadata.name: redline #161
metadata.description:
This is my second generative art project on fxhash. I wanted a project that offered more VARIETY compared for my first project so this is what I came up with: a clean and simple rectangles & lines project :D 

There are a few options for the number of columns that are generated: 3, 5, 7, 9, and each column is randomly filled with dense or alternating line patterns (sometimes no pattern!). 3 columns are common, the rest are less common. Having more than half the columns empty is relatively rare. Having all columns empty is extremely rare! 

Also I have to give credit to Tyler Hobbs, this piece was super inspired by an old IG post of his. Please enjoy!

metadata.name: The Passage #46
metadata.description:
There are always places where we want to go, where we want to be. But not all places are readily accessible for us. In order to enter through The Passage and go to wherever you'd like, you'll need to have the right passcode.

Know that some passages will always be closed for us, whether we have the passcode or not...

* * *

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART

metadata.name: Grud #11
metadata.description:
Grud, a speedrun on 31st May 2022. 

The cousin of the BoodMoards, exploring some other shapes, colours and fun ideas. 

Made with p5js. 
23 colour palettes
10 background colours 
11 tile styles 

Big thanks to all collectors and shoutout to the Circolors frens for the support <3 

10% of mint proceeds going to the processing foundation 
42% of royalties to minters. 

Click the image or press 's' or 'S' in live mode to save a 2160 × 2700 png
